Contribution Guidelines

We welcome contributions from all members of our community! To ensure a smooth and productive contribution process, please follow these guidelines:

Familiarize yourself with our project and its goals before contributing.

Check our issue tracker for any open issues related to your proposed contribution. If you do not find an existing issue, please create a new one.

If you are working on an existing issue, please comment on the issue to let us know you are taking it on.

Fork the project repository and create a new branch for your contribution.

Write clean, readable, and well-documented code.

Ensure your code follows our project's coding conventions and standards.

Write and run unit tests for your contribution.

Submit a pull request to the main project repository with a clear description of your changes.

Be responsive to feedback and be willing to make changes if necessary.

Please be patient with the review process. We strive to review all contributions in a timely manner, but it may take some time depending on the size and complexity of the contribution.

By contributing to our project, you agree to abide by our code of conduct. We reserve the right to reject any contribution that violates this code of conduct or does not meet our project's standards.

Thank you for your interest in contributing to our project!
